What is node ?
Open-source, cross platform runtime environment for executing the javascript code outside of a browse.
Addvantages
*Great for prototyping and agile development
*superfast and highly scalable
*javascript everywhere
*cleaner and more consistent codebase
\*Large eco-systems of open source libraries.

How node works ?
Non-blocking Aysnchronous nature of node
single thread is used to handle multiple requests
node will be monitoring Event queue at the backend to see if the request is ready.Once recieved it will server the request.
